    "domain_description": "The UKMLA Applied Knowledge Test assesses medical knowledge required for safe practice as a UK Foundation Doctor. Based on GMC Outcomes for Graduates and UK Foundation Programme Curriculum, it emphasizes clinical reasoning, patient safety, evidence-based practice, and integrated knowledge across specialties. Testing focuses on common presentations, diagnostic reasoning, management principles, prescribing safety, professional practice, and population health. Questions are case-based, testing application rather than recall, with emphasis on conditions commonly seen in UK practice.",
